---
const cards = [
  {
    headline: 'Your quote form only collects names.',
    body: "A basic contact form doesn't help the customer pick a service, understand packages, or take the next step.",
  },
  {
    headline: 'Customers ask for prices, then disappear.',
    body: "If quoting is slow, vague, or manual, they'll shop around before you ever reply.",
  },
  {
    headline: 'People choose the cheapest option.',
    body: 'Without clear packages and value framing, customers compare price instead of fit.',
  },
  {
    headline: 'Paid traffic lands on a weak page.',
    body: 'Sending Google Ads clicks to a generic homepage burns money before a visitor ever becomes a lead.',
  },
  {
    headline: "The site doesn't guide the customer.",
    body: "A real service page answers four things: what you do, who it's for, why trust you, and what to do next. Most don't.",
  },
];
---
<!-- PROBLEM SECTION -->
<section id="problem" class="relative border-b border-line">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> The Real Bottleneck</span>
      <h2 class="mt-5 text-[2rem] sm:text-[2.6rem] leading-[1.05] font-bold">
        Your Site Gets Visitors. Your Phone Doesn't Ring.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-text-soft text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed">
        Most service businesses don't have a traffic problem. They have a "what happens next" problem.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-soft text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed">
        A customer lands on the site. They scroll. They look at services. They want pricing. They find a contact form that asks for their name, email, and "how can we help?" — and they bounce. Off to the next shop on the list.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      {cards.map((c) => (
        <div class="card p-6 sm:p-7 flex flex-col gap-4">
          <h3 class="text-[1.15rem] leading-[1.3] font-semibold text-text">
            {c.headline}
          </h3>
          <p class="text-[0.95rem] text-text-soft leading-relaxed">{c.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-[1.05rem] sm:text-[1.15rem] leading-relaxed text-text">
        The fix isn't a prettier homepage. It's replacing the dead-end contact form with
        <span class="text-accent font-medium">a quote system that guides the sale</span>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- /PROBLEM SECTION -->
